      • decorateBeforeSerialization

        public ExtensionFeatureDescription decorateBeforeSerialization(ExtensionFeatureDescription o)
        Description copied from interface: ResourceDecorator
        This method is called to give this decorator an opportunity to change the content of the model object before it is serialized. A typical use is the obfuscation of sensitive data before it is sent to the client. By default, this method returns the same bean.
        Parameters:
        o - Model object
        Returns:
        Decorated object
